# Payment Shop — Core Design

Date: 2026-06-24  
Status: Approved (design)  
Scope: `frontend/src/games/regularPayments/`, `sui-tunnel-ts/src/protocol/`, `dopamint` Move (new module)

## Problem

The arena needs a **payment-first showcase** that demonstrates high-throughput
off-chain signing over Sui Tunnels — similar in _metering shape_ to Stripe/Tempo
streaming payments (many sub-cent transfers, settle once), implemented as a
**bilateral tunnel session** between a user and a shop counterparty.

**Payment Shop** lets users spawn **Random NFT machines**, stream micro-payments
to the shop until a price threshold is met, see an NFT reveal in the browser,
then settle once on-chain. The primary metric is **effective TPS**
(dual-signed tunnel steps per second).

## Goals

- **Self-play** demo: one browser holds both tunnel parties (User = A, Shop = B).
- **Random NFT only** — one item type, one machine card pattern.
- **One default machine** on enter; **Mint NFT** (+ icon) in the toolbar adds more
  (**no cap** on parallel machines per window).
- Each machine streams **micro-payments** (A → B) off-chain until usage ≥
  price target → status **Completed** → outcome chosen in the browser.
- **Two on-chain steps per machine session**: **open** (browser wallet) + **settle**
  (browser posts transcript to Backend **`/settle`**; close + NFT mint in that path).
- Narrow **vending / gacha machine** UI (`450px`–`640px` max width).
- Feed activity into arena **telemetry** (TPS chart, live feed).
- **Browser-owned randomness + metadata**: frontend holds a catalog array
  `{ imageUrl, titleNFT, shortDescription }`; user wallet passes the chosen row into
  the on-chain mint function at settle.

## Non-goals

- On-chain NFT mint or transfer **per micro-tick** (destroys the TPS story; all mint
  logic runs in the single settle transaction).
- Multi-party tunnels or lobbies (tunnels are strictly **party_a + party_b**).
- x402 / MPP / Tempo wire integration in v1 (metering reference only).
- PvP user-vs-user for v1 (self-play only; user-vs-shop PvP later).
- Modifying core `sui_tunnel::tunnel` — app logic lives in a wrapper module.
- Paying a separate fee or revenue share to the shop counterparty beyond the streamed
  purchase amount (shop B only uses its tunnel balance to execute the prepared mint).

## Concept

**Payment Shop** is a floating arena widget (`regular-payments`, `catalog: false`).
Users spawn **machine sessions** from the toolbar. Each session is an independent
bilateral tunnel where the user streams tiny balance shifts to the shop until a
fixed **price target** is paid. Every micro-transfer is one dual-signed off-chain
state update — the unit of TPS.

References (metering only, not wire format):

- Tempo/Stripe streaming payments demo.
- `sui_tunnel::example_tunnel_lifecycle` — micropayment session.
- `sui_tunnel::example_api_credits` — open → off-chain usage → close settle.
- `sui-tunnel-ts` `PaymentsProtocol` — highest-throughput fixed-size encoding.
- [2026-06-24-settle-binary-transcript-design.md](../specs/2026-06-24-settle-binary-transcript-design.md) —
  binary `/settle` body, **16 MB** cap, **`MAX_MOVES_PER_TUNNEL = 50_000`**.

