## Architecture

### Layers

| Layer                 | Responsibility                                                 | v1                             |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| **UI**                | `PaymentsWindow`, `MachineCard`, item bar, TPS footer          | New                            |
| **Session hook**      | `usePaymentShop` — array of machine sessions                   | New                            |
| **Session core**      | `stepMachine`, `deriveMachineView` (pure, React-free)          | New                            |
| **Protocol**          | `randomNft.v1` — micro-pay, completion                         | New in SDK                     |
| **Engine**            | `OffchainTunnel.selfPlay` per machine                          | Reuse                          |
| **On-chain (open)**   | Browser wallet — `open_session` / fund tunnel                  | Reuse `tunnelTx.ts`            |
| **On-chain (settle)** | Browser → Backend **`POST /settle`** → close + mint            | Reuse settler + new Move entry |
| **On-chain (NFT)**    | `dopamint::random_nft_shop::mint_random_nft` (3 metadata args) | New Move module                |
| **Telemetry**         | `TelemetryProvider` writer per tick                            | Reuse                          |

### Bilateral model (2-party only)

```
Party A  =  User (customer)
Party B  =  Shop / House
```

Each machine = **one tunnel**. “Transfer to server” = balance shift **A → B**
inside tunnel state. No third participant. Multi-machine = multiple independent
tunnels, not multiple users in one tunnel.

### Multi-machine = multi-tunnel (no window cap)

```
Click Mint NFT  →  tunnel_1 + MachineCard #1
Click Mint NFT  →  tunnel_2 + MachineCard #2
…
(unlimited parallel machines; UI scrolls)
```

Aggregate **global TPS** = sum of all running machine step loops.

### On-chain vs off-chain

| Phase                | Chain     | Who                   | Per machine                               |
| -------------------- | --------- | --------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Spawn (open + fund)  | On-chain  | **Browser wallet**    | 1 tx                                      |
| Micro-payment stream | Off-chain | Browser (self-play)   | N dual-signed steps                       |
| Close + mint NFT     | On-chain  | **Backend `/settle`** | 1 sponsored settle (bundles close + mint) |

**Settle transcript limits:** `/settle` bodies are capped at **16 MB**. The SDK
counts moves in-tunnel and must stop (or rotate) at **`MAX_MOVES_PER_TUNNEL` (50k)**
or when the encoded transcript would exceed **16 MB** — whichever comes first.
Payment Shop targets **1000** micro-pay moves per purchase, well inside both caps.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User UI (browser)
    participant W as User wallet
    participant OC as Off-chain engine
    participant B as Backend /settle
    participant C as random_nft_shop

    U->>W: open_session + fund (10 MTPS)
    W->>C: on-chain open tx
    Note over U: MachineCard Idle

    U->>OC: Start Stream
    loop each micro-tick (0.001 MTPS)
        OC->>OC: MICRO_PAY dual-sign A→B
        Note over U: usage++, TPS++
    end
    OC->>OC: usage >= price → completed
    Note over U: browser picks random catalog row

    U->>B: POST /settle (binary transcript + metadata)
    B->>C: close cooperative + mint_random_nft(imageUrl, title, desc)
    C->>W: NFT object to Party A
```

