## NFT reward & settlement

### Two-step reward (UI vs chain)

| Step             | Where                 | What user gets                                                          |
| ---------------- | --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Stream completes | Off-chain + UI        | Status **Completed**, browser-random catalog preview                    |
| Settle           | Backend **`/settle`** | Coin split from transcript + **NFT object** minted with chosen metadata |

Completing the progress bar does **not** mint on-chain. The NFT arrives only when
**`/settle`** succeeds.

### Balance math at close (coin)

Example: user deposits **10 MTPS**, `priceTarget = 1 MTPS`, shop starts at `0`:

| Party    | After stream                | After settle                                                                       |
| -------- | --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| A (user) | `9 MTPS` (unused budget)    | `9 MTPS` refunded                                                                  |
| B (shop) | `1 MTPS` (payment received) | Shop B balance used only to **pay mint gas / execute mint** — no extra fee to shop |

The streamed **1 MTPS** is the purchase. The NFT is the **reward**, minted in the
same settle transaction using shop B's address balance as the executing party.

### Move module: `dopamint::random_nft_shop`

Wrapper around `Tunnel<T>` (pattern: `example_api_credits`, `example_tunnel_lifecycle`).

**Open** — browser wallet calls `open_session(deposit_a, party keys, price_target, micro_unit)`:
creates tunnel, deposits user **10 MTPS** budget, shares session object.

**Mint (single entry point)** — exposed to the settler after transcript verify:

```move
public fun mint_random_nft(
    image_url: String,
    title_nft: String,
    short_description: String,
    // + tunnel close / balance witnesses per wrapper pattern
)
```

No per-tier mint table in v1 — one function, three string params, as prepared on
the contract side. Shop does not receive a separate fee; mint is funded from shop B's
tunnel/settler context.

Core `tunnel::close_cooperative` is **not** modified. NFT delivery is app-layer only.

### Claim UX

| Mode                        | Behavior                                                           |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Manual settle** (default) | Completed card shows **[Claim NFT]** → browser calls **`/settle`** |
| **Auto-settle** (optional)  | Frontend posts settle when stream completes                        |

Recommend **manual settle** for real wallets (explicit user confirm). Auto-settle
acceptable for self-play demo.

