## User flow

### Primary flow (Random NFT)

| Step | User action                                    | System                                                         |
| ---- | ---------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1    | Open **Payment Shop** → intro → **Enter shop** | Toolbar + empty or default card                                |
| 2    | Click **Mint NFT**                             | Browser **open** tx → **Machine card** (`spawning` → `idle`)   |
| 3    | Click **Mint NFT** again                       | Another tunnel + card (no max)                                 |
| 4    | **Start Stream** on a card                     | `running`; micro-pays tick; usage rises                        |
| 5    | Usage ≥ price                                  | `completed`; browser-random catalog preview                    |
| 6    | **Claim NFT**                                  | **`POST /settle`** → close + `mint_random_nft(...)` → `closed` |
| 7    | **Pause** (optional)                           | Stop loop; tunnel stays open                                   |
| 8    | **✕** on card                                  | Dismiss UI only if not completed; otherwise require settle     |

### Status machine (per card)

```
spawning → idle → running → completed → closed
                ↑      ↓
              pause ───┘
```

| Status      | UI        | Meaning                                    |
| ----------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `spawning`  | Opening…  | Browser open tx in flight                  |
| `idle`      | Idle      | Tunnel ready; stream not started           |
| `running`   | Running   | Micro-payment loop active                  |
| `completed` | Completed | Price paid; preview shown; ready to settle |
| `closed`    | Closed    | Settled on-chain; NFT delivered            |

### Mint NFT = open + render (combined)

**Mint NFT** click always:

1. Calls browser **open** (fund **10 MTPS**).
2. Appends `MachineCard` to scrollable list.
3. Does **not** auto-start stream — user presses **Start** on the card (prototype may auto-stream).

